# Use Tailwind CSS
- Always use Tailwind utility classes instead of CSS modules
- Never import or use .module.css files
- Use semantic class names with Tailwind's utility-first approach
- Example mappings:
  - overlay → fixed inset-0 bg-black bg-opacity-50 flex items-center justify-center z-50
  - popup → bg-white rounded-lg p-6 min-w-[300px] max-w-[500px] shadow-lg
  - error → text-red-600
  - success → text-green-600
  - confirm → text-blue-600
  - actions → flex justify-end gap-3 mt-4
  - button → px-4 py-2 rounded font-medium
  - button-primary → bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors
  - button-secondary → bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-300 transition-colors